What assurance does it suit me?
Motor insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible claims, involves a significant expenditure which will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of the driver's licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or use of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
Y es que, escoger el seguro de automóvil adecuado es incluso más diffícil que elegir el modelo de vehículo.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance, is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is materialized by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in return becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a loss.
The premium is the price of insurance, which takes into account various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of the driver's licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or use of it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so that the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the score to be paid.
It is for this reason that people over the age of 25 and women must pay lower premiums, since statistics show that these people have a lower rate of claims due to their prudence.
Similarly, using censuses, the companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency and thus the likelihood of an accident.
By increasing the frequency the probability increases.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
That's why the driver needs to study the situation carefully to choose the car insurance that best fits his profile.
We will present here the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers it a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face a variety of disadvantages when entering into a contract with insurance at an affordable price, as can be the low experience in driving and the seniority of the driver's licence.
Although the ideal way to be well insured is risk insurance, other, more cost-effective options exist.
The most forward-looking drivers can opt for any risk insurance with a deductible, so that they get coverage from any risk insurance but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the claim that the customer pays will be determined according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount," says Luis Noguera, the Spanish head of First Europa, an online insurance mediator.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fires and loss of the vehicle.
A piece of advice.
If you are under 25 years of age try to be careful and avoid claims to the extent possible, since this will affect the bonus, which can reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the company's basic rate.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic tariff.
"The subsidies and penalties will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses", clarifies Noguera.
Beyond the age of 25 this becomes easier for drivers when contracting with insurance, since the loss rate is reduced thanks to accumulated experience.
It is for this reason that it is preferable to choose an all-risk insurance with deductible.
"Normally young people cannot take advantage of the experience acquired in advance after an accident", says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is preferable for the client to negotiate insurance at any risk, as long as his or her economic situation allows him or her to do so.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be those with the lowest claim rate, because the increases will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be any risk insurance with deductible (may be 300 euros), or an extended third-party insurance from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
"They have a more relaxed drive and they have greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of assuming a larger amount of franchises," says Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, a risk-free insurance policy is preferable (i.e. 150 euros), or an extended third-party insurance policy when the insurer has a high level of subsidy.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, but also because it represents a major expense, which is why it is essential to study properly the insurance that suits us most according to our personal situation.
