He referred to the expected decision of the Sports Federation in early December, regarding Munich's bid for the 2018 Winter Games.
This preference means for us, that in the period we had planned until 2028 until then, we will have no chance."
However the dream does not definitely belong to the past, said Von Beust.
The Hamburg Sports Federation (HSB) regretted Beust's statements.
From this the impression would be given that Hamburg no longer wants to apply for the Olympic Games in the next 25 years.
"It's too early to close an opportunity, burying the projects already now," said HSB President Günter Ploß on Wednesday.
An abandonment of the candidature would also be in contradiction with the statements of the head of the Senate on the occasion of the reception in plenary assembly of the German Federation of Higher Schools of Sport.
There, Von Beust would have qualified Hamburg's bid for the 2015 Universiades as "not a substitute" for the Hamburg Olympics.
The Federation of Higher Schools of Sport had first in the past weeks named Hamburg as a candidate city.
