"The development of Little Grasbrook was denied by the Senate for years because it played the Olympiad card and excluded housing construction," said SPD delegates Carola Veit and Jan Quast.
While the SPD has always called for the Petit Grasbrook to have a plan integrated into the Olympiads and a subsequent use of housing, the CDU would have relied exclusively on the "Event factor".
The bid for the 2012 Summer Olympics, for its part, would have raised great enthusiasm in Hamburg.
